<article class="bordered-top info">
  <h2 class="title row">Our Coffee</h2>
  <div class="row">
    <%= image_tag "latte_art.jpg", :class => "four columns" %>
    <div class="eight columns">
      <p>We take great pride in preparing our coffee and have the pleasure of working with local London roasteries who support direct trade methods of purchasing coffee, resulting in a  range of high quality of coffees on offer, all roasted to perfection using delicate roasting profiles.</p>

      <p>Our house espresso is the Rogue from <a href="http://www.unionroasted.com/">Union Hand-Roasted Coffees</a>. Developed with Andrew Tolley of Taylor St Baristas, the components of Rogue change on a seasonal basis which ensure a great tasting product at all times of the year.</p>

      <p>Our guest espresso, decaf and filter coffee is provided by <a href="http://shop.squaremilecoffee.com/">Square Mile Coffee Roasters</a>. What we offer in store will constantly change to showcase their stunning range of coffees.</p>

      <p>For more details ask our baristas what is currently being featured.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>

<article class="bordered-top info">
  <h2 class="title row">Our Tea</h2>
  <div class="row">
    <%= image_tag "tea.jpg", :class => "four columns" %>
    <div class="eight columns">
      <p>Our teas are supplied by tea traders <a href="http://www.lalaniandco.com/">Lalani &amp; Co</a> who spend time every year visiting tea farms around the world to source only the highest quality teas. We brew our teas in homemade <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gaiwan">Gaiwans</a> using exact recipes to ensure we get the best out of the leaves.</p>

      <p>We also make a fresh mint infusion made from our mint garden grown in store. We have a range of mint including Applemint and Black Peppermint so ask our staff what they can offer you.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>

<article class="bordered-top info">
  <h2 class="title row">Our Food</h2>
  <div class="row">
    <%= image_tag "sandwich.jpg", :class => "four columns" %>
    <div class="eight columns">
      <p>Our food menu is designed around the concept of having simple options made from good quality ingredients.</p>

      <p>Our Pastries are supplied by <a href="http://www.yeastbakery.com/">Yeast Bakery</a> who are uncompromising in their pursuit of creating the perfect croissant.</p>

      <p>The remainder of our food which includes delicious sweet and savoury muffins, decadent brownies and custard tarts, classic tasty sandwiches made on a range of breads and fresh seasonal salads, come from <a href="http://twitter.com/#!/brownsofse4">Browns of Brockley</a>.</p>

      <p>For more information on our current food offering and enquiries for office catering please email <a href="mailto:food@curatorscoffee.com">food@curatorscoffee.com</a>.</p>
    </div>

  </div>
</article>

<article class="bordered-top info">
  <h2 class="title row">Design</h2>
  <div class="row">
    <%= image_tag "cabinet.jpg", :class => "four columns" %>
    <div class="eight columns">
      <p>The concept of Curators Coffee developed from our attempts to visualise the art of coffee and our desire to create a gallery space for our craft. A collaboration between talented furniture builder Jason, of madebyjason and designer extraordinaire Jen Archer led to Curators Coffee Studio, a space of free thought, where things are collected and recreated or reimagined. To reflect this weâ€™ve used a mix of recycled, new and artisan materials to bring this to life.</p>
    </div>

  </div>
</article>
